Concurrently, India is bolstering its maritime security posture in the Indo-Pacific by hosting the expanded 'Malabar Plus' naval exercise. This multilateral drill includes not only the Quad partners but also select ASEAN nations, underscoring India's commitment to regional stability and interoperability among friendly navies.

On the climate front, India has pledged an increased financial contribution to the Green Climate Fund (GCF). This move reinforces India's leadership in global climate action and serves as a strong call for developed nations to fulfill their long-standing climate finance commitments, emphasizing the principle of Common but Differentiated Responsibilities.

